    q: "Will a VPN slow down my internet speed?",
    a: "Yes, because your traffic is encrypted and routed through an additional server, a VPN will usually reduce your internet speed. However, top-tier providers like NordVPN and ExpressVPN use optimized protocols (like WireGuard or Lightway) that make the speed drop virtually unnoticeable for most daily tasks."
  },
  {
    q: "Are free VPNs safe to use?",
    a: "Most free VPNs are not safe. They often log your data, sell it to advertisers, inject ads into your browsing, or even carry malware. The only safe free VPNs are the limited 'freemium' tiers offered by reputable paid providers, such as ProtonVPN or Windscribe."
  },
