    q: "What does 'No-Logs Policy' actually mean?",
    a: "A true no-logs policy means the VPN provider does not record or store your IP address, browsing history, bandwidth usage, or connection timestamps. The best VPNs have their no-logs claims verified by independent third-party audits (like Deloitte or PwC) to prove they aren't storing user data."
  },
  {
    q: "Can a VPN guarantee total anonymity?",
    a: "No. A VPN provides privacy, not complete anonymity. It hides your IP address and encrypts your traffic, but you can still be tracked through browser fingerprinting, cookies, or if you log into accounts (like Google or Facebook) while connected. For extreme anonymity, tools like the Tor browser are required."
